04-637X/807/1/45/apj515339ieqn6.gif] \$0.21\_-0.06{\textasciicircum}+0.11\$ super-Earths per M dwarf HZ. This suggests that the nearest potentially habitable non-transiting and transiting Earth-size planets are 2.6 ± 0.4 pc and \#\#IMG\#\# [http://ej.iop.org/images/0004-637X/807/1/45/apj515339ieqn7.gif] \$10.6\_-1.8{\textasciicircum}+1.6\$ pc away, respectively. If we include super-Earths, these distances diminish to 2.1 ± 0.2 pc and \#\#IMG\#\# [http://ej.iop.org/images/0004-637X/807/1/45/apj515339ieqn8.gif] \$8.6\_-0.8{\textasciicircum}+0.7\$ pc.},
